# Admin auth — agent reference

Applies whenever a change touches the `/bookings` routes, the new admin-only edge functions, or anything that used to be gated by `?dev=true` / `?testing=true`.

## 1. Auth model

- Provider: **Supabase Auth** with **Google OAuth**.
- Client: `@supabase/supabase-js` (add to `ui/package.json` when implementing).
- Single shared Supabase client: `ui/src/lib/supabaseClient.ts`.
- Entry point: a new `/sign-in` route that calls `supabase.auth.signInWithOAuth({ provider: 'google', options: { redirectTo: <origin>/bookings } })`.

## 2. Allow list

- Only these emails may access admin routes and admin edge functions:
  - **Config**: `ADMIN_ALLOWED_EMAILS` — comma-separated env var in `supabase/.env.local` and Supabase dashboard.
  - **Default value**: `kamehome.azurenorth@gmail.com`.
- The allow list is enforced **server-side** on every admin edge function via `_shared/auth.ts#verifyAdminJwt(req)`. Never trust the client.
- Client also reads `ADMIN_ALLOWED_EMAILS` (via `VITE_ADMIN_ALLOWED_EMAILS`) for an immediate UX reject, but never as the only gate.

## 3. Route guards (UI)

- New component: `ui/src/features/admin/components/RequireAdmin.tsx`.
  - Shows a loader while the session hydrates.
  - Redirects to `/sign-in` if unauthenticated.
  - Shows a generic "access restricted" message if the signed-in email is not allow-listed (no disclosure of which emails are allowed; signs the user out from that view).
- Applied to: `/bookings`, `/bookings/:bookingId`, and any other admin route added later.
- The existing public routes (`/`, `/form`, `/success`, `/calendar`) stay unauthenticated.

## 4. Dev mode & testing mode — new rules

The old query-parameter controls go away:

- ❌ `?dev=true` — removed. An admin session automatically enables dev controls on guest-form views.
- ❌ `?testing=true` — removed from the public form. Replaced by a dedicated **Test Submit** button available only when the admin session is active (or when the environment is non-production).
- ✅ **Admin session implies dev mode.** When `useAdminSession()` reports an authenticated admin, the guest form shows the dev controls panel and the Test Submit button.
- ✅ **Non-production envs** (`import.meta.env.VITE_NODE_ENV !== 'production'`) still show dev controls without requiring admin login for local development.

### Submit button semantics

| Button            | Behavior                                                                              |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Submit**        | Real booking. Server sets `status = PENDING_REVIEW`, `is_test_booking = false`.       |
| **Test Submit**   | Test booking. Server sets `is_test_booking = true`, keeps status `PENDING_REVIEW`, and runs the **exact same test pipeline as today’s `testing=true`** (prefixes, PDF copy, email subject prefixes, calendar/sheet markers, prod email hard-off rules — unchanged). |

Test bookings:

- Prefix `[TEST] ` on primary guest name, storage objects, calendar/sheet titles, **email subjects**, PDF title tweaks — same as current `isTestingMode` behavior in `submit-form` + `_shared/*`.
- Are filtered out of `/bookings` by default (toggleable filter).
- **Never send email in production**, regardless of other toggles (`DENO_DEPLOYMENT_ID` + `is_test_booking` ⇒ force `sendEmail = false`).
- Are subject to `cleanup-test-data` wipe.

## 5. Dev controls panel (admin detail page)

Shown on `/bookings/:bookingId`. Checkbox list driving what happens on the next action click:

| Checkbox                          | Shown when                  | Replaces the old            |
| --------------------------------- | --------------------------- | --------------------------- |
| Save to database                  | always                      | `saveToDatabase`            |
| Save images to storage            | always                      | `saveImagesToStorage`       |
| Generate PDF                      | always                      | `generatePdf`               |
| **Send GAF request email**        | always                      | renamed from `Send email notification` |
| **Send Parking broadcast email**  | only when `need_parking`    | new                         |
| **Send Pet request email**        | only when `has_pets`        | new                         |
| Update Google Calendar            | always                      | `updateGoogleCalendar`      |
| Update Google Sheets              | always                      | `updateGoogleSheets`        |

All checkboxes start **unchecked**. In production they are authoritative — flipping them off means "really don't do it".

## 6. Server contract

- All admin edge functions (`list-bookings`, `transition-booking`, `upload-booking-asset`, `parking-broadcast-email`) set `verify_jwt = true` in `supabase/config.toml` and must call `verifyAdminJwt(req)` as the first line of the handler.
- The public functions (`submit-form`, `get-form`, `get-booked-dates`) keep `verify_jwt = false` — guests must still be able to hit them with only the anon key.

## 7. Env vars summary (new)

| Var                               | Scope | Purpose                                          |
| --------------------------------- | ----- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| `ADMIN_ALLOWED_EMAILS`            | edge  | Comma-separated allow list (server-enforced).    |
| `VITE_ADMIN_ALLOWED_EMAILS`       | UI    | UX reject only; never the only gate.             |
| `PARKING_OWNER_EMAILS`            | edge  | Comma-separated BCC list for parking broadcast. Initial seed list lives in `docs/NEW_FLOW_PLAN.md` §6.1 Q4.1 — **never hardcode emails in source**; rotate via env only. |
| `GMAIL_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID`           | edge  | Gmail listener OAuth.                            |
| `GMAIL_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET`       | edge  | Gmail listener OAuth.                            |
| `GMAIL_OAUTH_REFRESH_TOKEN`       | edge  | Gmail listener OAuth (for `kamehome.azurenorth`).|
| `SD_REFUND_CRON_GRACE_MINUTES`    | edge  | Default `15`; post-checkout grace period.        |

Remember to update `docs/PROJECT.md` §11 Environment variables in the same commit that introduces any of these.

## 8. Don'ts

- Don't pass JWTs or admin emails through URL query strings.
- Don't add a second Supabase client — share `ui/src/lib/supabaseClient.ts`.
- Don't hardcode `kamehome.azurenorth@gmail.com` in code; read from env.
- Don't build admin features that work without `verifyAdminJwt` server-side — the allow list is the one real gate.
